= Pastek =

A powerfull lighweight markup language

This is version 20140125.

== Syntax ==

Title             = words = (closing '=' are optionnal)
List              # words
                    -- words
                    -- words
                       --- words
                  # words
                  (identation is optionnal, number of symbols define depth)
                    
Image (?)         [[filename.jpg]]
Link (?)          [[label url]]

Bold              **words**
Italic            //words//
Underline         __words__
Strike            --words--
Monospaced        ``words``

Table             +-----------------------------+ (optionnal)
                  |  head1  |  head2  |  head3  | (optionnal
                  +-----------------------------+  pair)
                  | cell1.1 | cell1.2 | cell1.3 |
                  | cell2.1 | cell2.2 | cell2.3 |
                  +-----------------------------+ (optionnal)
		  (pipes, plus and minus do not have to match)

Subscript         _i (one sign)
                  _{index} (several signs)
Superscript       ^i (one sign)
                  ^{index} (several signs)

Codeblock         ```
                  let triple_backquoted =
                    "Code block"
                  ```

External command  ```dot
                  graph graphname {
                      a -- b -- c;
                      b -- d;
                  }
                  ```

Source code       {{{<span style="color:blue">Inline source code.</span>}}}
                  {{{
                  <p style="color:red">
                  Introduce source code in your document.
                  </p>
                  }}}